x4freetext: 179.3+-0.8 MeV proton beam on enriched Li-7
Residual proton beam current monitoring by Faraday cup.
Distance between Li-7 target and center of Medley
chamber - 4618 mm, where neutron beam has 42.08 mm
and low energy tail. Spectrum is given on :
TOF gate reduces the low energy contribution; fraction
of neutrons in the low energy tail, including a 2%
contribution from frame overlap, accounts for 50% of
Neutron spectrum was measured with proton recoil
technique, at 20 degrees in the lab. system , using
TOF - to select peak neutrons and reject tail
neutrons. Fight path of about 4.5 m.
TOF of each CP from reaction target at the Medley
centre to first SIBAR is subtracted from the total TOF.
Instrumental background was measured without sample.
TOF FWHM of (n,p) elastic peak at 20 deg. in the lab.
system, measured from CH2 target with 175 MeV QMN,
is equal to 8.8 ns. Repetition time between beam
micropulses is of the order of 45 ns.
TFBC and IOCH - for relative neutron beam
Medley spectrometer consist of eight three-elements
telescopes mounted in evacuated cylindrical chamber of
90 cm diameter. Each telescope consists of two fully
depleted silicon surface barrier detector (served as
1000 microm thick) and CsI(Tl) scintillator (as E
detector, 50 mm diameter, 100 mm length) with
by Geant and PHITS codes showed that all produced light
ions fully stop in CsI(Tl) detector.
Medley can detect protons  from 2 up to 170 MeV,
Thresholds for other ions are higher, up to 9 MeV for
